  <context>
    <background>
      Phase A tasks 006 and 009 renamed `IAnalysisToolHandler` to `IToolHandler` and
      split the execution context (`ToolExecutionContext` for playbook; `ChatInvocationContext`
      for chat). The 8 typed handlers (FR-13 through FR-20) implement against the
      renamed interface and split contexts. Before Wave 1 + Wave 2 can run in parallel,
      a shared contract + test fixture must exist so each handler PR does not invent its
      own registration pattern, mock layout, or telemetry-assertion style.

      The existing `GenericAnalysisHandler.cs` is the canonical reference for what a
      handler looks like end-to-end; it is auto-discovered today. This task verifies that
      mechanism + extends the fixture so the 8 typed handlers all share identical
      scaffolding.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/HandlerRegistrationConventions.md (NEW — 4-point contract doc)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/TypedToolHandlerTestFixture.cs (NEW — shared test fixture)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/HandlerContractTestTemplate.cs (NEW — template each handler test copies)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/AutoDiscoveryVerificationTests.cs (NEW — verifies auto-discovery picks up all IToolHandler implementations)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <related-work>
      <item>Phase A task 006 — `IAnalysisToolHandler` → `IToolHandler` rename. Hard dependency.</item>
      <item>Phase A task 009 — `ToolExecutionContext` + `ChatInvocationContext` split. Hard dependency.</item>
      <item>Wave 1 tasks 101–104 — pure-deterministic handlers; depend on this task.</item>
      <item>Wave 2 tasks 105–108 — LLM-assisted handlers; depend on Wave 1 starting.</item>
      <item>Task 109 — dispatch tests; depends on Wave 2 complete.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context usage. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then request `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Foundational handler infrastructure; gates 9 downstream tasks (101-109)
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`; confirm task 100 status is 🔲; dependencies (006, 009)
      are complete. Read `current-task.md` to verify no prior R6 task is in flight.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract from
      `GenericAnalysisHandler.cs` the existing registration shape; from
      `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` the auto-discovery mechanism; from `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`
      the binding governance rules for BFF additions.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify Auto-Discovery Works Today">
      Confirm `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` currently auto-discovers `IAnalysisToolHandler`
      (now `IToolHandler` after task 006) implementations via assembly scan. If not,
      ADD the auto-discovery mechanism inside the module (ZERO new top-level DI lines).
      Write `AutoDiscoveryVerificationTests.cs` that asserts all `IToolHandler` types
      in the assembly are resolvable from the service provider.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author HandlerRegistrationConventions.md">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/HandlerRegistrationConventions.md`.
      Document the 4-point contract verbatim: (1) implements `IToolHandler`; (2) registered
      via auto-discovery — no manual DI line; (3) has corresponding `sprk_analysistool`
      Dataverse row with `sprk_handlerclass` matching the C# class name; (4) ships
      contract + positive + error + config-driven tests using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`.
      Include a worked example using `GenericAnalysisHandler` as the canonical reference.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author TypedToolHandlerTestFixture">
      Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/TypedToolHandlerTestFixture.cs`.
      Provide shared mocks (`Mock&lt;IOpenAiClient&gt;`, `Mock&lt;IScopeResolverService&gt;`),
      `BuildToolExecutionContext(...)` + `BuildChatInvocationContext(...)` helpers, and
      `AssertTelemetryRespectsAdr015(...)` helper that asserts logged events contain
      handler name + execution outcome + timestamp ONLY and never user input text.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Author HandlerContractTestTemplate">
      Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/HandlerContractTestTemplate.cs`.
      Provide an `[Fact]`-driven template each handler test class copies: (a) handler
      type is registered in DI; (b) handler is resolvable by `sprk_handlerclass` lookup;
      (c) handler metadata is non-null + version is semver; (d) `SupportedToolTypes` is
      non-empty.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Run Tests">
      Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`.
      Confirm all tests pass including the new `AutoDiscoveryVerificationTests`.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
      Measure compressed output. Report absolute size + diff vs prior baseline (~45.65 MB)
      in task notes. Expected delta ≤+0.2 MB (only the conventions .md doc ships in
      binary as embedded resource if at all; test fixture does not).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and record evidence in task
      notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new files (conventions .md, test fixture,
      template, verification tests, any auto-discovery additions). Run `adr-check` skill
      against the same files; verify ADR-010 (DI minimalism), ADR-013 (handler placement),
      ADR-015 (telemetry surface), ADR-029 (publish-size). Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 100 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md` to the next pending handler task (or first of Wave 1). Confirm
      Wave 1 (101–104) is now unblocked. Report task completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

